      <h3>Code Showcase &mdash; Joseph Method (<small>updated 5/6/08</small>)</h3>
      <p>I am a programmer who specializes in <a href="http://ruby-lang.org">Ruby</a>, <a href="http://rubyonrails.org">Ruby on Rails</a> and web development in general. This page is meant to showcase some of my recent programming work and skills.</p>

      <!-- Ruby -->
      <div class="programming-type">
        <div class="programming-type-header">Ruby Code</div>
        <div id="ruby-section" class="programming-type-body hideable">
          <ul>
            <li><a href="http://alexandria.rubyforge.org">Alexandria Book Library Manager</a> &mdash; I am a principal administrator of this opensource project (a GUI application for the Linux desktop). I maintain a Ruby on Rails-based wiki on my server <a href="http://wiki.alexandria-projects.org">here</a>. <small>svn records <a href="http://rubyforge.org/scm/?group_id=205">here</a>.</small> <a href="screenshot-alexandria.png" rel="lightbox[showcase]" title="Alexandria Screenshot 1"><small>screenshot</small></a>, <a href="screenshot-alexandria-2.png" rel="lightbox[showcase]" title="Alexandria Screenshot 2"><small>screenshot</small></a></li>
            <li><a href="http://gitorious.org/projects/agile-lamp">Agile Lamp Utility</a> &mdash; an opensource project providing a software client for a commercially available USB lava lamp. <small>Link is to a git repository</small>. <a href="screenshot-agilelamp.png" rel="lightbox[showcase]" title="Agile Lamp Screenshot"><small>screenshot</small></a></li>
            <li>Findrate &mdash; a complex Ruby on Rails project enabling mortage brokers to aggregate mortgage rates from banks. Proprietary code. <a href="image-0.png" rel="lightbox[showcase]" title="Findrate Banks Page"><small>screenshot</small></a>, <a href="image-1.png" rel="lightbox[showcase]" title="Findrate Banks Page"><small>screenshot</small></a></li>
            <li><a href="http://www.lplato.com">LPlato Website</a> &mdash; Simple website in English and Chinese using altered template and a Ruby on Rails <a href="http://radiantcms.org">CMS</a>. Dynamic header and sidebar change based on page URL.</li>
          </ul>
